ns2:PrimaryTypeDefinition.ns1:desc: This Managed Object contains a GERAN cell

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The value component of the Relative Distinguished Name (RDN).
Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.
PLMN ID supported by the cell.

The Location Area Code of the external GERAN cell. A fixed-length code identifying the location area within a PLMN. Refer to 3GPP TS 23.003. Special values: The values 0 and 65534 are reserved for special cases where no valid Location Area Identity (LAI) exists in the network.
Cell Identifier that is unique within the context of the GERAN location area. Refer to 3GPP TS 23.003.
Base station Colour Code (BCC). BCC and NCC together denote the physical cell identity for the GERAN cell (that is the Base Station Identity Code, BSIC).
Network Colour Code (NCC). BCC and NCC together denote the physical cell identity for the GERAN cell (that is the Base Station Identity Code, BSIC).
Label for free use.
Indicates whether the MO has been created by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator.
Indicates the date and time when the MO was created by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS
The identity of the GeranCell represented by this MO, particularly for automatically created ExternalGeranCell managed objects. The masterGeranCellId is set to the Full Distinguished Name (FDN).

This parameter indicates if the external GERAN cell is RIM capable. If the value is RIMIncapable, no attempt will be made to create a RIM association to the external GERAN cell, other values will result in a attempt to create a RIM association.
This parameter indicates the current status of the RIM association to this external cell.

Indicates if the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function is allowed to remove this object. It does not restrict operator removal of the object. Objects created by ANR have this parameter set to true initially.
Indicates whether the MO has been last modified by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator.
The date and time when the MO was last modified by the Automated Neighbor Relations (ANR) function or operator. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS
The Routing Area Code of a routing area. The value -1 of the attribute is used to mark that no vaild routing area code has been defined.
This attribute describes the Dual Transfer Mode (DTM) capability of the external cell.
